                    <div class="ArticleSummary font_color" id="article-text">
                     <a class="rss vtip" href="http://rss.wn.com/English/publication/The+Examiner" title="The Examiner RSS"></a>
					<a href="http://www.examiner.com/biker-culture-in-albany/the-ghost-rider-all-of-us" class="resultsource">The Examiner</a>
                     <span class="date">2012-02-21</span>: 

	                     <span dir="ltr" lang="en"><a href="http://wn.com/Having" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Having</a> seen the movie, &ldquo;<a href="http://wn.com/Ghost_Rider" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Ghost Rider</a> <a href="http://wn.com/Spirit_of_Vengeance" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Spirit of Vengeance</a>,&rdquo; this weekend, I came away with a lot to think about.  This and the first movie are based on that always-popular theme of "<a href="http://wn.com/Good_vs._Evil" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Good vs. Evil</a>," and this one was just as dark as the first.  <a href="http://wn.com/Gone" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Gone</a> was the dashing <a href="http://wn.com/Sam_Elliott" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Sam Elliott</a> as the centuries-old Ghost Rider, and another actor replaced <a href="http://wn.com/Peter_Fonda" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Peter Fonda</a> as the <a href="http://wn.com/Devil" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Devil</a>, but he was just as effective.   <a href="http://wn.com/Watching" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Watching</a> <a href="http://wn.com/Nicolas_Cage" target="_blank" class="a_keyword_link">Nicolas Cage</a> in this role is fascinating because he embodies the character so well &ndash; rough-around-the-edges biker with a tortured soul and a huge heart.  There he is with his</span>...	
	                 <a href="http://www.examiner.com/biker-culture-in-albany/the-ghost-rider-all-of-us" class="resultsource">more &raquo;</a>
