        <h1 class="firstHeading" id="firstHeading">
			Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance
		</h1>
		
        <div style="line-height: 20px;"><!--!ignored:For-->
<table class="infobox"><tr><th>name</th><td>Ghost Rider:<!--!ignored open tags-->Spirit of Vengeance</td></tr><tr><th>director</th><td><a href="http://wn.com/Neveldine_Taylor" title="Neveldine/Taylor">Neveldine/Taylor</a></td></tr><tr><th>producer</th><td><a href="http://wn.com/Ashok_Amritraj" title="Ashok Amritraj">Ashok Amritraj</a><!--!ignored open tags-->Ari Arad<!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Avi_Arad" title="Avi Arad">Avi Arad</a><!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Michael_De_Luca" title="Michael De Luca">Michael De Luca</a><!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Steven_Paul" title="Steven Paul">Steven Paul</a></td></tr><tr><th>screenplay</th><td><a href="http://wn.com/Scott_Gimple" title="Scott Gimple">Scott Gimple</a><!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Seth_Hoffman" title="Seth Hoffman">Seth Hoffman</a></td></tr><tr><th>story</th><td><a href="http://wn.com/David_S_Goyer" title="David S. Goyer">David S. Goyer</a></td></tr><tr><th>based on</th><td><em><a href="http://wn.com/Ghost_Rider_comics_" title="Ghost Rider (comics)">Ghost Rider</a></em> by <!--!ignored:nowrap--></td></tr><tr><th>starring</th><td><a href="http://wn.com/Nicolas_Cage" title="Nicolas Cage">Nicolas Cage</a><!--!ignored open tags-->Fergus Riordan<!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Ciar_n_Hinds" title="Ciarán Hinds">Ciarán Hinds</a><!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Violante_Placido" title="Violante Placido">Violante Placido</a><!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Idris_Elba" title="Idris Elba">Idris Elba</a><!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Christopher_Lambert" title="Christopher Lambert">Christopher Lambert</a><!--!ignored open tags--><a href="http://wn.com/Johnny_Whitworth" title="Johnny Whitworth">Johnny Whitworth</a></td></tr><tr><th>cinematography</th><td>Brandon Trost</td></tr><tr><th>editing</th><td><a href="http://wn.com/Brian_Berdan" title="Brian Berdan">Brian Berdan</a></td></tr><tr><th>studio</th><td><a href="http://wn.com/Columbia_Pictures" title="Columbia Pictures">Columbia Pictures</a><!--!ignored open tags-->Hyde Park Entertainment<!--!ignored open tags--><!--!ignoredBrackets:Image--></td></tr><tr><th>distributor</th><td>Columbia Pictures</td></tr><tr><th>released</th><td><!--!ignored:Film--></td></tr><tr><th>country</th><td><!--!ignored:Film--></td></tr><tr><th>language</th><td>English</td></tr><tr><th>budget</th><td>$50,000,000</td></tr><tr><th>gross</th><td>}}</td></tr></table>

<p>
<strong><em>Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance</strong></em> is an upcoming <a href="http://wn.com/3D_film" title="3D film">3D</a> <a href="http://wn.com/superhero_film" title="superhero film">superhero film</a> based on the <a href="http://wn.com/Marvel_Comics" title="Marvel Comics">Marvel Comics</a> supernatural antihero <a href="http://wn.com/Ghost_Rider_comics_" title="Ghost Rider (comics)">Ghost Rider</a>, scheduled to be released in theaters on February 17, 2012. The film is  a loose <a href="http://wn.com/sequel" title="sequel">sequel</a> to the 2007 film <em><a href="http://wn.com/Ghost_Rider_film_" title="Ghost Rider (film)">Ghost Rider</a></em>.<!--!ignored html tags--><!--!ignored html tags--> It will be directed by <a href="http://wn.com/Mark_Neveldine" title="Mark Neveldine">Mark Neveldine</a> and <a href="http://wn.com/Brian_Taylor_filmmaker_" title="Brian Taylor (filmmaker)">Brian Taylor</a>. Cage will reprise his role as <a href="http://wn.com/Ghost_Rider_Johnny_Blaze_" title="Ghost Rider (Johnny Blaze)">Johnny Blaze / Ghost Rider</a>. It is the second film to be released under the Marvel Knights banner after 2008's <em><a href="http://wn.com/Punisher_War_Zone" title="Punisher: War Zone">Punisher: War Zone</a></em>.
</p>

<p>
<h2>Premise</h2>
Set several years after <a href="http://wn.com/Ghost_Rider_film_" title="Ghost Rider (film)">the first film</a>, Johnny Blaze is in self-imposed exile from the world.  Blaze has become a tormented soul, convinced that his powers are a curse. Former stuntman Blaze is then approached by Moreau, a member of the monastic order of Michael, the warrior angel. Moreau seeks a protector for a mother and son duo who are being pursued by a figure named Roarke – a fellow with a detailed knowledge of the Ghost Rider and his different identities over the centuries.<!--!ignored html tags-->
</p>

<p>
<h2>Cast</h2>
<!--!ignoredhtmlcomment:-->
<li> <a href="http://wn.com/Nicolas_Cage" title="Nicolas Cage">Nicolas Cage</a> as <a href="http://wn.com/Ghost_Rider_Johnny_Blaze_" title="Ghost Rider (Johnny Blaze)">Johnny Blaze / Ghost Rider</a></li>
 <a href="http://wn.com/Johnny_Whitworth" title="Johnny Whitworth">Johnny Whitworth</a> as <a href="http://wn.com/Blackout_comics_Half_demon" title="Blackout (comics)#Half-demon">Roarke Carrigan / Blackout</a>: The antagonist who, at the beginning, is human. He is turned into Blackout by the Devil to complete his job (which is not specified). This transformation gives him the fortitude and supernatural abilities to compete with Ghost Rider.<!-- !ignored html tags --> 
<li> Fergus Riordan as Danny</li>
 <a href="http://wn.com/Ciar_n_Hinds" title="Ciarán Hinds">Ciarán Hinds</a> as <a href="http://wn.com/Devil" title="Devil">The Devil</a>: Who is trying to take over the body of his son on the boy's birthday.<!-- !ignored html tags --> It is not clear whether this is intended to be the same character as <a href="http://wn.com/Peter_Fonda" title="Peter Fonda">Peter Fonda</a>'s <a href="http://wn.com/Mephisto_comics_" title="Mephisto (comics)">Mephisto</a> from the previous film.
 <a href="http://wn.com/Violante_Placido" title="Violante Placido">Violante Placido</a> as Nadya<!-- !ignored simplehtml tags -->
 <a href="http://wn.com/Idris_Elba" title="Idris Elba">Idris Elba</a> as Moreau<!-- !ignored html tags -->
 Tobias Öjerfalk  in an unknown role.<!-- !ignored html tags -->
 <a href="http://wn.com/Christopher_Lambert" title="Christopher Lambert">Christopher Lambert</a> as a monk:<!-- !ignored html tags --><!--!ignored html tags--> He was required to undergo "sword training for 3 months"<!--!ignored html tags--> and shave his head.<!--!ignored html tags-->
</p>

<p>
<h2>Production</h2>
<h3>Development</h3>
On February 9, 2007, Marvel producer <a href="http://wn.com/Avi_Arad" title="Avi Arad">Avi Arad</a> announced the development of <em>Ghost Rider 2</em> at a press event.<!--!ignored html tags--> Peter Fonda has also expressed a desire to return as <a href="http://wn.com/Mephisto_comics_" title="Mephisto (comics)">Mephistopheles</a>.<!--!ignored html tags--> In early December, 2007, Nicolas Cage also has expressed interest to return in the lead role as Ghost Rider.<!--!ignored html tags--> Shortly after, in another interview he went on further to mention that he would enjoy seeing a darker story, adding, "He's not eating jelly beans anymore; he's getting drunk". He suggested that the film could do with newly created villains.<!--!ignored html tags--> It is also rumored that the sequel would feature <a href="http://wn.com/Danny_Ketch" title="Danny Ketch">Danny Ketch</a>, another Marvel character who takes up the Ghost Rider mantle.<!--!ignored html tags-->
</p>

<p>
<!--!ignored:Quote-->
</p>

<p>
In a September 2008 interview, Nicolas Cage informed <a href="http://wn.com/IGN" title="IGN">IGN</a> that Columbia have taken meetings to start a sequel. Cage noted conversations about the story, where Ghost Rider may end up in Europe on behalf of the church, having story elements "very much in the <a href="http://wn.com/zeitgeist" title="zeitgeist">zeitgeist</a>, like <em><a href="http://wn.com/The_Da_Vinci_Code" title="The Da Vinci Code">Da Vinci Code</a></em>."<!--!ignored html tags--> In February 2009, an online source stated Columbia Pictures had greenlit a sequel to <em>Ghost Rider</em>. Nicolas Cage will reprise the lead role, whilst the studio are in search of writers.<!--!ignored html tags--> On September 23, 2009, it was reported that <a href="http://wn.com/David_S_Goyer" title="David S. Goyer">David S. Goyer</a> signed on to write the script for the sequel.<!--!ignored html tags--> Goyer spoke to <a href="http://wn.com/MTV" title="MTV">MTV</a> about the sequel, stating that the story will pick up eight years after the events of the first film and that he hopes to start filming by 2010.<!--!ignored simplehtml tags--><!--!ignored html tags--> The sequel is entitled <em>Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance</em> and will be produced by Mike De Luca<!--!ignored html tags--> and will screen with a PG-13 rating.<!--!ignored html tags--> On July 14, 2010 it was confirmed that Nicolas Cage would return, and <a href="http://wn.com/Mark_Neveldine" title="Mark Neveldine">Mark Neveldine</a> and <a href="http://wn.com/Brian_Taylor_filmmaker_" title="Brian Taylor (filmmaker)">Brian Taylor</a> were in negotiations to direct.<!--!ignored html tags-->
</p>

<p>
In February 2011, Cage revealed that Spirit of Vengeance will not be a sequel to 2007's Ghost Rider, and will even feature a new origin sequence.<!--!ignored html tags-->
</p>

<p>
<h3>Filming</h3>
In July 2010 Cage revealed shooting was to start in November.<!--!ignored html tags--> In an interview with <a href="http://wn.com/Superhero_Hype_" title="Superhero Hype!">Superhero Hype!</a>, <a href="http://wn.com/Eva_Mendes" title="Eva Mendes">Eva Mendes</a> revealed that she would not be back as Roxanne for the sequel.<!--!ignored html tags--> The film will be shot in <a href="http://wn.com/3_D_film" title="3-D film">3-D</a> in <a href="http://wn.com/Romania" title="Romania">Romania</a> and <a href="http://wn.com/Turkey" title="Turkey">Turkey</a>.<!--!ignored html tags--> The film started <a href="http://wn.com/principal_photography" title="principal photography">principal photography</a> in <a href="http://wn.com/Bucharest" title="Bucharest">Bucharest</a>, <a href="http://wn.com/Romania" title="Romania">Romania</a> in November 2010, using mostly local talent.<!--!ignored simplehtml tags--> Principal photography was completed on January 24, 2011.<!--!ignored html tags--> On March 16, 2011, it was confirmed that <a href="http://wn.com/Johnny_Whitworth" title="Johnny Whitworth">Johnny Whitworth</a> would be playing the antagonist, which was also confirmed to be Blackout.<!--!ignored simplehtml tags-->.
</p>

<p>
Three scenes were shot on set Castel Film. Among the places in the country chosen were împrejurimilesale, <a href="http://wn.com/Transf_g_r_an" title="Transfăgărăşan">Transfăgărăşan</a>, <a href="http://wn.com/Targu_Jiu" title="Targu-Jiu">Targu-Jiu</a>, Hunedoara Castle and <a href="http://wn.com/Bucharest" title="Bucharest">Bucharest</a>.<!--!ignored html tags-->
</p>

<p>
Filming in Turkey took place in <a href="http://wn.com/Cappadocia" title="Cappadocia">Cappadocia</a>, a historical region in central Turkey with exotic chimney topped rocky setting.
</p>

<p>
<h2>Promotion</h2>
The official trailer for the film went online on August 2011. <!--!ignored html tags-->
</p>

